<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-12-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-21"><hi rend="italic">December 21,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(As Mr. Conger has felt obliged to acquiesce in the note retaining
                                the word “irrevocable,” and considering his statement that if he
                                does not sign it will probably result in failure of negotiations,
                                Mr. Hay authorizes him to sign after again stating the views of this
                                Government.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>